ZURICH. Brazil surged to the top of the FIFA world rankings for the first time in seven years yesterday, made all the sweeter as they usurped great rivals Argentina. It caps a terrific week for forward Neymar and Brazil last week they became the first country to qualify for the 2018 World Cup in Russia, their latest step on the road to redemption after the embarrassment and heartache of their World Cup failure on home soil in 2014.Brazil were dumped off top spot after their elimination from the 2010 World Cup in South Africa.Their surge is in contrast to the struggles of Argentina and Neymar s Barcelona team-mate Lionel Messi, whose country are in danger of missing out on next year s World Cup. They will not be able to call on their star man for three of their four remaining qualification matches because of suspension.Third in the newly released rankings are world champions Germany, followed by Chile and Colombia.Switzerland enter the top 10, up to ninth, with former number ones Spain clinging on in 10th. AFP.